Next, we will use the Japanese Yen to buy a dollar since the exchange rate is ¥114 = $1. Therefore, we will divide ¥ 116.6739 by the spot exchange rate of Can ¥ 114 to determine the value of U.S dollar we can get.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{U.S. Dollar \$} &= \dfrac{\text{¥ to be exchanged}}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[10pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{¥ 116.6739}}{\text{¥ 114}}\\[10pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 1.0235}}
\end{aligned}$$
